<Author>talblet
<Content>Just like being in a friend's house Stayed three nights in this great hotel. Great location near the Ku'damm. Owners and all staff really friendly and very welcoming on arrival, including welcome drink. The whole place feels like home from comfortable home. We had keys to main front door, hotel front door and our room naturally. We had room 5 which was terrific and very spacious. Splendid shower after walking our socks off round this enormous, fascinating town. Breakfasts were delicious. Loads of tourist info and suggestions from the owners as to how and what to see. Honesty Bar open whenever we got back. We recommend going in December with all the wonderful Christmas Markets including the gluhwein and wonderful street decorations - makes London look v. boring in comparison. All in all a wonderful city beak in a lovely small and intimate hotel. 
