<Author>garbo
<Content>Wonderful boutique hotel My husband and i had a great stay at the Hotel Art Nouveau last summer. The owners of the small property are very friendly and go out of their way to help you with your travel plans. The hotel is close to the train line, that can take you to Brandenburg gate, reichstag and other key sites. The hotel is in a mostly residential neighorhood, which is full of great restaurants. There is a german pub across the street and an Italian restaurant around the corner. There is a gas station/convenience store adjacent to the hotel, which was great to pick up a map, drinks, or snacks. The hotel is on the fourth floor of an old art nouveau building. You take a lovely antique lift to the hotel. The breakfast was really nice. Cereals, breads, meats, cheeses, juices, all the standard European fare. One great thing, is in the afternoon and at night, the breakfast room has an honor system. They have wine, beer and other drinks in their fridge. You just write down what you had and they charge it to your room. Plus normal prices! We had a very comfortable room with ensuite bathroom. The room had an antique chest in it with wooden floors. Lovely large windows that opened up to the back of the property. The only downside of this place and it wasn't their fault, was that we were there during a heatwave and it was unbelieveably hot. Like most hotels in Europe, that aren't business class, they don't have airconditioning or fans. They have a simple computer with free internet. Wasn't working very well when we were there, but i am sure it's fine now. Otherwise a great stay and i would highly recommend this hotel. 
