<Author>travelman1938
<Content>Charming, friendly Berlin headquarters The combination of location, style, charm, value and warmth of welcome have made the Art Nouveau my Berlin headquarters for the past 10 years. HIgh ceilings, spacious rooms, big windows, hardwood floors, and interesting art. If you're there to enjoy the city, owners Christine and Gerd Schlenzka will point you in the right direction. They know all the neighborhood restaurants (many good ones) and Christine stays current on Berlin's vibrant art scene. On my last visit they recommended a special lunch deal at the Michelin-starred restaurant in the Swissotel. It was an extrordinary 3-course meal for about 25 euros. They also sent us to Rogacki, a fabulous Berlin seafood bar known only to locals. Very off the beaten path and inexpensive. Example: three fresh Normandy oysters and a generous glass of white wine for a mere 7 euros. I saw quibbles in a previous post about small TVs, no fresh juice, and lukewarm coffee. If those things are really important go to one of the boring, impersonal chain hotels where you'll pay an extra 20 euros for breakfast...but the TV will be good. I've been traveling frequently in Germany for 30 years. This place is a gem...a throwback. Soon all the family-owned hotels will be run out of busines by the Mercures and Novotels of the world. BTW, my coffee's always been hot. 
