<Author>selmrl
<Content>Doesn't Live Up To The Hype Recognizing that hotel experiences are highly subjective and that many of the reviews of Hotel Art Nouveau are positive, I wanted to share our mediocre experience. I'm not really sure why the hotel is named what it is. I noted a couple of art nouveau pieces, but the only item in our room that clearly was of that period was a single nightstand. Everything else is, well, just a hodgepodge of disparate styles.We stayed in the suite called Peter for a week. It's the strangest suite I've been in. One enters through the kitchen and the fold-out bed/sitting room is in the kitchen as well. Looking at the floor plan in the breakfast room, I noticed that some of the regular rooms were larger than our suite. Also, if you stay in Peter, don't plan to sleep past 8:00 during the week. There is an elementary school next door and the kids raise quite a racket first thing in the morning. If 8:00 is your wake up time, no need for an alarm clock. Closing the double windows blocks out the noise pretty well, but then you lose the fresh air.The breakfast buffet is okay. I've had better and worse.The owners had some very good restaurant recommendations and we liked the neighborhood. Pretty easy to get around by train, subway or bus.So, overall, I rate our experience here as average which was disappointing. My expectations were higher based on others' reviews. 
