<Author>Hodkinson
<Content>My home from home in the Berlin :-) This is one of the most enjoyable hotel stays I've had!Why? Because it didn't feel like I was staying in a hotel! This is a lovely old Jugendstil or Art Nouveau building (hence the name) with more character than any hotel chain would ever offer you. The Schlenzkas give you freedom to have your stay largely on your own terms and do not charge the earth for it either. We stayed in the Red 'Christina' Suite which was just perfect in every way for us. A good sized living room with wonderful chaise longue and modern bathroom and a bedroom to die for - all minimalistically furnished with a mix of classic antique and modern pieces , but with ample storage space and a stunning bed. Unlike many hotels, we were not pushed into the breakfast room before 9AM and on to the street by 10 by the cleaners - instead you could have breakfast any time up to 10:30 and the cleaning staff came to service the room when it was convenient for you to have it done!I'd recommend it to anyone looking to slow the pace of their trip down and relax into life in Berlin. With great local restaurants like Tavola Calda and the numerous options on offer in the bustling Savigny Platz and it's off-shoot streets only 10 minutes walk away, you are never far away from your brunch or evening meal! Another 15 minutes on the S-Bahn takes you to Hackescher Markt where your evening can really get into full swing.I'll be back in Berlin soon and I'll be back at Hotel Art Nouveau!! 
