<Content>Excellent Value. Caring Owners. We spent three nights at Hotel Art Nouveau in July. It's located on the 4th floor of a lovely, restored art nouveau building just off the Ku'damn, near alot of good restaurants and stores. Safe, upscale neighborhood. The owners are very friendly, helpful and generous. The breakfast room offers free coffee, tea and snacks 24/7, and an honor bar (reasonably priced). The only downside is no air conditioning, but heat waves are rare in Berlin. The rooms are comfortably but do vary in size and design, so it's better to request a specific room from their website. We would not hesitate to stay again. 
