<Content>Beware - unscrupulous business practices! I feel it is important to warn travelers about deciding to stay at the Hotel Art Nouveau in Berlin based on our experience: My husband and I were traveling to Germany for our wedding, and we wanted to stay one night in Berlin with my parents. After reading reviews, we made reservations at the Hotel Art Nouveau. Fifteen days before we were suppose to stay at the hotel, our plans changed, and my husband immediately called to cancel our reservations. The staff person (who later we believe was the Hotel Art Nouveau owner) said, Good! Thank you for calling and letting us know and we hope you will stay with us later. There was no discussion that we needed to follow-up with a written cancellation and we trusted all would be well.However, our next creditcard statement included a charge for $250 for both rooms we had reserved. We contacted the Hotel Art Noveau. The owner immediately told us we had no proof of ever calling. When we contacted the phone company and provided proof of a call on the date we had told him we had cancelled, he said that proving that we called did not provide proof that we had cancelled the rooms.The Hotel Art Nouveau owner also told us to look on their Web site and at the bottom of their emails where it says in small writing all cancellations must be written HOWEVER, while all other reservation information is in English and German, the written requirement is only in German at the very bottom of each screen not easy to find. When we pointed out this fact, the owner agreed it was misleading and said that he would no longer communicate with us about the charge.Our concern is how many non-German-speaking travelers have made reservations with the Hotel Art Noveau and then cancelled by phone only later to be charged for their rooms and then forced to pay ..... I warn all those who seek to stay at the Hotel Art Noveau to be extremely careful and not become victims to unscrupulous business practices. 
